pageContext.claim: “We've created over 7 million jobs since the election -- a number that would be unthought of. If I ever said that during the campaign -- you know the feeling -- they would have gone after me very strongly, huh?”
pageContext.analysis: The number is roughly 7 million. But jobs grew at a faster rate during the last three years of Barack Obama's term, compared with Trump's first three years in office, so it was hardly "unthought of."
